🔹 Core Workflow Integration
Instead of spinning up VMs or running live desktop traces to catch edge cases, you execute your agent loop mentally or via text simulation against algebraic rules. At each step, you check threshold conditions, apply latency/penalty math, and predict exact environment responses before touching real hardware. This turns debugging from trial-and-error into deterministic trace logic.

