🔹 Step-by-Step Application Guide
Define Your Target Stack
Replace Aegis ZS2 + Win11 with your actual machine specs. Keep the 3-layer structure: HW envelope → OS contract → Overlay composition rules.

Ingest via Prompt or Context Manager
Paste relevant layers into your agent’s system prompt, meta-reasoning layer, or config schema. Use structured formats (JSON/YAML) for reliable LLM parsing.

Run Textual Execution Trace
Step through each agent action (capture() → decide() → click()/type()). Apply algebraic rules at every transition:

IF VRAM ≥ threshold → latency_multiplier × base
IF DPI scale ≠ 1.0 → gx = monitor_x + (ix * scale)
IF focus_loss > N → trigger fallback chain
Tune Your Reliability Engine
Map overlay triggers directly to agent fallback logic: dynamic quantization, context truncation, retry limits, or graceful aborts. Make thresholds configurable per workload.

Generate Deterministic Test Matrices
Convert rules into failure injection scenarios for CI or manual validation:

VRAM 14.0→14.3GB → offload penalty applied
QoS switched to Balanced → 2.8× latency injection
Secondary monitor disconnected → coordinate origin shift +540px
